headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 25 points and 11 rebounds in 29 minutes, and the Boston Celtics cruised to a 122-102 victory over the Washington Wizards on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown help Celtics rout Wizards 122-102 in first road game

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 28 points and 10 rebounds, Klay Thompson added 22 points in his Dallas debut and the Mavericks beat the San Antonio Spurs 120-109 in the opener for both teams Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 28, Thompson adds 22 in Dallas debut as Mavs top Spurs 120-109

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 28 points, Chet Holmgren added 25 as part of a stellar all-around performance and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Denver Nuggets 102-87 on Thursday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Holmgren lead Thunder to 102-87 win over Nuggets in season opener
